<div class="page-content">
  
  <h2>What Is a DØLL?</h2>
  <p>A DØLL is a creator on the PAY THE DØLLS marketplace. Artists. Musicians. Designers. Builders. Makers. Visionaries.</p>
  <p>If you're trans, queer, or adjacent, and you're creating something worth selling — you're a DØLL.</p>
  
  <h2>Why Join PAY THE DØLLS?</h2>
  
  <p><strong>Keep most of your money.</strong><br>
  70-80% of every sale goes directly to you. We take 20-30% to keep the lights on and fund the next creator through Verse Capital.</p>
  
  <p><strong>Your own storefront.</strong><br>
  paythedolls.com/dolls/[yourname] — a branded page showcasing your work, your story, and your products.</p>
  
  <p><strong>Marketing and infrastructure.</strong><br>
  We handle the platform, payment processing, customer service, and community marketing. You focus on creating.</p>
  
  <p><strong>Access to Verse Capital.</strong><br>
  Need funding for your next project? DØLLs get priority consideration for grants.</p>
  
  <p><strong>Community and support.</strong><br>
  Join a network of trans and queer creators building together. Share resources. Collaborate. Grow.</p>
  
  <p><strong>No upfront costs.</strong><br>
  No application fees. No monthly fees. No inventory requirements. We only make money when you make money.</p>
  
  <h2>Who Should Apply?</h2>
  
  <p><strong>You're a good fit if:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>You identify as trans, nonbinary, queer, or gender expansive</li>
    <li>You have products or services to sell</li>
    <li>You're committed to quality and professionalism</li>
    <li>You align with our values of community and reinvestment</li>
    <li>You want to be part of a growing ecosystem</li>
  </ul>
  
  <p><strong>Categories we're looking for:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Merch (apparel, accessories)</li>
    <li>Art (prints, originals, digital)</li>
    <li>Beauty (makeup, skincare, fragrances)</li>
    <li>Music (vinyl, digital, merch)</li>
    <li>Prints (posters, wall art)</li>
    <li>Services (styling, creative direction)</li>
    <li>Home goods (mugs, towels)</li>
    <li>Experiences (events, workshops)</li>
  </ul>
  
