  <h2>How It Works</h2>
  
  <p><strong>1. APPLY</strong><br>
  Fill out the application below. Tell us about yourself, your work, and what you want to sell.</p>
  
  <p><strong>2. REVIEW</strong><br>
  We review applications on a rolling basis. We're looking for quality, alignment, and readiness to sell.</p>
  
  <p><strong>3. ONBOARDING</strong><br>
  If approved, we'll help you set up your storefront. Product photography tips. Copywriting support. Brand guidelines.</p>
  
  <p><strong>4. LAUNCH</strong><br>
  Your storefront goes live. We announce you to the community. You start selling.</p>
  
  <p><strong>5. GROW</strong><br>
  We provide ongoing marketing support, community access, and potential funding through Verse Capital.</p>
  
  <h2>What You Keep vs. What We Take</h2>
  
  <p><strong>You keep: 70-80% of gross sales</strong><br>
  This is your money. Direct deposit. Weekly or monthly payouts.</p>
  
  <p><strong>We take: 20-30%</strong><br>
  This covers:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Platform fees (Shopify, payment processing)</li>
    <li>Operations and customer service</li>
    <li>Marketing and community building</li>
    <li>Verse Capital contributions (funding the next DØLL)</li>
  </ul>
  
  <p><strong>Example:</strong><br>
  You sell $1,000 in products.<br>
  You keep: $700-800<br>
  Platform costs: ~$50-100<br>
  Verse Capital contribution: $100-200<br>
  Operations: $50-100</p>
  
  <h2>Application Requirements</h2>
  
  <p><strong>About You:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>Name and pronouns</li>
    <li>Location (city/state)</li>
    <li>Social media handles</li>
    <li>Brief bio (2-3 sentences)</li>
  </ul>
  
  <p><strong>About Your Work:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>What do you create?</li>
    <li>What categories are you selling in?</li>
    <li>Do you have products ready to sell now?</li>
    <li>Links to portfolio/website/social media</li>
  </ul>
  
  <p><strong>About Your Store:</strong></p>
  <ul>
    <li>What will you sell on PAY THE DØLLS?</li>
    <li>Do you have product images ready?</li>
    <li>Estimated launch timeline</li>
    <li>Anything else we should know?</li>
  </ul>
  
  <h2>FAQ</h2>
  
  <div class="faq-item">
    <p class="faq-item__question">Do I need to have inventory ready?</p>
    <p class="faq-item__answer">Not necessarily. Print-on-demand and made-to-order products are fine. But you should be ready to fulfill orders within 2 weeks of launch.</p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="faq-item">
    <p class="faq-item__question">Can I sell on other platforms too?</p>
    <p class="faq-item__answer">Yes. We don't require exclusivity. Sell wherever you want.</p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="faq-item">
    <p class="faq-item__question">What if I'm not ready to launch yet?</p>
    <p class="faq-item__answer">Apply anyway. We'll keep your application on file and reach out when you're ready.</p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="faq-item">
    <p class="faq-item__question">Is there a minimum or maximum price for products?</p>
    <p class="faq-item__answer">No minimum. We recommend pricing your work fairly and competitively.</p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="faq-item">
    <p class="faq-item__question">Can I update my storefront after launch?</p>
    <p class="faq-item__answer">Yes. Add new products, update copy, change images anytime.</p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="faq-item">
    <p class="faq-item__question">Do you help with product photography?</p>
    <p class="faq-item__answer">We provide guidelines and tips. Professional photography is your responsibility, but we can connect you with resources.</p>
  </div>
  
